<Layouts.app current_path={@conn.request_path}>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-prose mx-auto px-6 md:px-8">
      <header class="mb-12 text-center">
        <.heading level={1}>About Me</.heading>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <.text variant={:lead} class="text-justify">
          Hiya! I'm currently working as as product engineer at <.link href="https://incident.io">incident.io 🔥</.link>, a company in the incident industry. Even though I'm primarily working with Go and TypeScript now, my heart is still with Elixir. I'm a big fan of the Elixir programming language and community and I've been a pretty frequent speaker at conferences.
        </.text>

        <.text class="text-justify">
          I've also done a stint as a direct of engineering at an ad tech company, staying hands on by building a bespoke revenue optimizing adapter to sit between Out of Home screens and ad exchanges. I've also worked with travel, focused on high throughput CPU intensive processing as a staff engineer, but more importantly, on starting up and leading teams, taking them from zero to productivity and supporting my coworkers with mentoring and coaching. Before that I did cyber security, building Cloudflare workers that could run between your app and your clients and seamlessly apply intelligent rules to deny fraudulent login attempts. I also spent a few years working for a health tech company in Sweden. All in all I've got over 14 years of professional software engineering experience.
        </.text>

        <.text class="text-justify">
          Although I live in London 🇬🇧 I spend a lot of my time in Mexico 🇲🇽
        </.text>

        <.text class="text-justify">
          You can find me on Bluesky at <.link
            href="https://bsky.app/profile/jola.dev"
            class="underline"
          >@jola.dev</.link>.
        </.text>

        <.sponsor title="Like what I do?" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layouts.app>
